      "message": "I see what it does, it's just that it does not seem related at all to 'exposing prometheus metrics' and while reviewing it's very confusing. \n\nAnd still, `await` returns Future, so it's effect is not immediate. When you are not returning this Future, you are changing the behavior quite a lot.\n\nSo to do \"exactly same thing\" you would need to write `override fun await() = ctx.channel().closeFuture().await()`",
